    "original_title": "Combination of locusts and water shortage devastate Mudug farmers",
    "slug": "locust-infestation-and-drought-destroy-crops-in-mudug-region",
    "summary": "Farmers in Hero-Dhagahley village, Mudug, face total crop loss due to locusts and water shortages, with one farmer reporting $1,300 in damages.",
    "content": "Farmers in Hero-Dhagahley village, located in Somalia's central Mudug region, are grappling with severe agricultural losses caused by a dual crisis of locust infestations and drought. The combination has destroyed crops, vegetables, and fruit that were nearing harvest, leaving many families without income or food supplies.\n\nAbdimaciin Ahmed Mahmoud, a local farmer, lost approximately $1,300 worth of produce from his two-hectare farm, which included tomatoes, onions, carrots, peppers, and lemons. He reported that locusts laid eggs in his fields and swarmed every plant, while insufficient water prevented him from saving the harvest. Other farmers in the village have experienced similar devastation.\n\nThe locust outbreak, which began earlier this year, has been exacerbated by unusually dry conditions in the region. Mudug has historically faced periodic droughts, but the simultaneous infestation has compounded the challenges for subsistence and small-scale farmers. Local authorities have yet to announce assistance measures.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, this crisis highlights ongoing vulnerabilities in rural food production and the urgent need for support systems that can mitigate such compound disasters. Many diaspora families rely on remittances to aid relatives in these regions, and crop failures could increase economic strain. Understanding these events helps the diaspora advocate for targeted aid and sustainable agricultural practices.\n\nThe situation in Hero-Dhagahley reflects broader climate-related challenges across Somalia, where erratic weather patterns and pests threaten food security. Without timely intervention, the region may face further hardship in coming months.\n\nRead the original report from Radio Ergo here: https://radioergo.org/en/2026/07/combination-of-locusts-and-water-shortage-devastate-mudug-farmers/",
