    "content": "Somalia’s Minister of Defence Ahmed Mohamud Fiqi has visited Amman, Jordan, where he held talks with Jordanian Chief of Staff General Yousef Al-Huneiti. The meeting took place as part of an official visit aimed at deepening ties between the two nations.\n\nDuring the discussions, the officials focused on enhancing bilateral military cooperation and addressing shared security challenges in the region and beyond. A statement from the Jordanian Armed Forces confirmed that both sides reaffirmed their commitment to expanding joint efforts in areas such as army training and capacity building.\n\nThe visit comes amid ongoing efforts by Somalia to strengthen its security institutions and receive external support against violence. Jordan has historically been a partner in regional security initiatives, and this engagement highlights the growing bilateral relationship.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, this agreement signals potential improvements in Somalia’s security sector, which directly impacts stability in the homeland and, consequently, the diaspora’s ability to engage with and invest in Somalia. Enhanced military cooperation with a experienced partner like Jordan also offers hope for more effective peacekeeping and counterterrorism operations.\n\nRead the original report from Goobjoog here: https://goobjoog.com/2026/07/15/soomaaliya-iyo-urdun-oo-xoojinaya-iskaashiga-dhinaca-difaaca-iyo-tababarka-ciidamada/",
